  "description": " Original Post ** Part 1 I\u0026rsquo;ve been talking about it in deeply Western terms but from my perspective a lot of what I\u0026rsquo;m thinking about is just variants of, how do I explain the deeply Christian ideology of many things that believe themselves to be secular and atheist, including lots of people who strongly emotionally identify with their existence as Other-than-Christian and take every bit of aesthetic and belief they can see in themselves as evidence that\u0026rsquo;s true.\n",
